SIMPLE: premature
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Premature
<hw>Pre`ma*ture"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praematurus</ets>; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>maturus</ets>
ripe. See <er>Mature</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Mature or ripe before
the proper time; <as>as, the <ex>premature</ex> fruits of a
hotbed</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Happening, arriving, existing, or performed before
the proper or usual time; adopted too soon; too early; untimely; <as>as,
a <ex>premature</ex> fall of snow; a <ex>premature</ex> birth; a
<ex>premature</ex> opinion; <ex>premature</ex> decay.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Arriving or received without due authentication or
evidence; <as>as, a <ex>premature</ex> report</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pre`ma*ture"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pre`ma*ture"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prematurity</ent>⟦br⟧
